remarks.remarkText: Nmrs birds on and in vcnty of airport.
Asde-x in use. opr transponders with alt rprtg mode and ads-b (if equipped) enabled on all airport sfcs.
Airport closed to aircraft with wing span over 125 ft excp 24 hours ppr, call amgr 713-845-6555.
Pilots/crew should be aware of dep turns in excess of 180 degs. read back of drctn of turns is highly encouraged.
Taxiway g cntrln to parked aircraft on west side only 68 ft. taxiway g cntrln to edge of adj svc vehicle road on west side only 48 ft.
Due to complex runway confign; when tax to thrs 13l & 13r check compass hdg bfr departing.
Aircraft southbound on taxiway c to runway 31l thr use extreme care; taxiway c makes a 45 deg dogleg to the left xng taxiway k.
Aircraft in takeoff ptn on runway 22 be alert for poss radio intfc or null on freq 118.7. use upper ant if so equipped.
Runway 13R controlling object clearance slope: Approach ratio 36:1 to dsplcd thr.
